wikipedia_page.main: Henry Davis (16 December 1803 – 29 February 1848) was an English cricketer who was recorded in one first-class match in 1826 when he played for a combined Sheffield and Leicester team, scoring 27 runs in his only innings and holding one catch. Davis played for Leicester Cricket Club from 1823 to 1839.
